# Styling: cls only, no inline style or hand-written CSS

- **Do not use `style=` on any element.** Use only the `cls` attribute with UnoCSS utility classes.
- **Do not add or maintain hand-written CSS** (e.g. in `static/*.css` or any `.css` file). All styling must come from:
  - `cls` in Python components, and
  - Generated `static/uno.css` (run `npm run build:css` or `npm run dev:css`).
- **Global resets or one-off rules** belong in `uno.config.ts` under `preflights` (e.g. button reset, layout overrides), not in a separate `.css` file.
- If a class is missing from `static/uno.css`, run `npm run build:css` (or remind the user to run it).
